          <Base:Description type="brief">
             bass crumhorn
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="examine">
             This is a bass crumhorn, a member of the double reed family. It is about a yard long, curved like a letter 'J', with a large windcap (protector) at the top, a straight stem over an inch thick with the finger holes, and the curving bell. It is made almost entirely of dark wood.
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="glance">
             A crumhorn.
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="look">
             A musical instrument, about a yard long and a inch in diameter. It has six finger holes along its length, and a slightly flared bell mouth.
          </Base:Description>
